The article is a Presidential Proclamation by Barack Obama, celebrating the 40th anniversary of the National Environmental Policy Act (NEPA). NEPA was signed into law in 1970 and has played a significant role in promoting environmental awareness and citizen participation in government. The proclamation emphasizes the importance of NEPA in protecting the environment and preserving it for future generations. The proclamation also highlights the role of NEPA in promoting economic prosperity and sustainable use of natural resources. The American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 reaffirmed NEPA's role in protecting public health, safety, and environmental quality. The proclamation calls upon executive branch agencies to promote public involvement and transparency in implementing NEPA. It also encourages all Americans to learn more about NEPA and contribute to protecting and enhancing the environment.